# Translation & billing tier scope (InterpreterAI)

## Do not change (final boss / OpenAI)

- **Platinum** and **`unlimited`** translation, prompts, finalize behavior, retries, or client paths tied to those plans.
- **OpenAI trial tiers:** default **`trial`** and **`trial-openai`** (same OpenAI `/translate` stack as Platinum). Do not modify their behavior, prompts, or shared OpenAI-only code paths except to fix unrelated bugs with explicit user approval.

## Allowed to change (Libre / machine translation only)

- **`basic`**, **`professional`**, and **`trial-libre`** only: server Libre path (`useMachineTranslation` in `transcription.ts`), `basic-pro-translate.ts`, `libretranslate.ts`. **Client translation dispatch must stay identical to Platinum** — engine swap is server-side only.

## Implementation discipline

- When editing shared files (e.g. `transcription.ts`), **gate** new behavior with `useMachineTranslation` (or equivalent) so **Platinum and OpenAI trials stay unchanged** unless the user explicitly asks otherwise. **Do not** add Basic/Professional-only branches in `use-transcription.ts` — same client flow for all plans.
- After completing requested work, **commit and push** to `main` unless the user says not to.
